energy.usef.agr.workflow.altstep

Class AgrReCreatePrognosesStubBoth

  • java.lang.Object
    • energy.usef.agr.workflow.altstep.AgrReCreatePrognosesStubBoth
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WorkflowStep

    public class AgrReCreatePrognosesStubBoth
extends Object
implements WorkflowStep
    Stub implementation of the PBC which is in charge of deciding to re-create or not A-Plans and or D-Prognoses after the re-optimization of the portfolio. This version recreates both the A-Plans and D-Prognoses.

    The PBC receives the following parameters as input:

    • LATEST_D_PROGNOSES_DTO_LIST : the list of latest Prognosis of type 'D-Progosis'.
    • LATEST_A_PLANS_DTO_LIST : the list of latest Prognosis of type 'A-Plan'.
    • CURRENT_PORTFOLIO : the current (and hence latest) portfolio with connection information.
    • CONNECTION_GROUPS_TO_CONNECTIONS_MAP : a map with a list of connection entity addresses per connection group.

    The PBC must output two flags indicating whether A-Plans and/or D-Prognoses must be re-created. These parameters have to be present and have to be named:

    • REQUIRES_NEW_APLANS_FLAG : boolean value indicating the re-creation of A-Plans
    • REQUIRES_NEW_D_PROGNOSIS_SEQUENCES_LIST : List of Long that are the sequence numbers of the D-Prognoses which will be re-created.
